args: Is that how you speak to a dragon such as\nmyself? Find your own work.
But you're the one who said I had to work!\nYou cannot simply leave me figuratively\ndead in the water after that.

I can and will. In fact, I already rescued
you from drowning once, and even went
so far as to procure clothes for you to
disguise yourself.
The rest is up to you.
Damn you, you heartless pactwyrm!\nEr, or ex-pactwyrm, I suppose.
Everyone keeps telling me to work,\nbut where am I even supposed to start?
You there! Lickspittle! Where are all of\nmy new soldiers?!

I'm afraid we had far fewer volunteers than
we'd hoped for, Your Majesty. Er, and we
also don't appear to have the budget to
increase our armaments either.
Of course! That's it! I just have to\n＂volunteer＂ my amazing services!
Well then, haste makes waste,\nso Operation: Get a Job begins now!
Rejoice, peon! I, the great Emperor Emile,\nhave decided to work in your employ!
You still on about that emperor business?\nYou're an adult, friend—best quit playing\npretend and join us in the real world.
Why, you insolent little... I AM the one true\nemperor, you dolt! By all rights, you should\nbe the one serving me!

You've got some serious attitude for a fella
what can't even pay his bill. But I've been
hurting for staff lately, so if you really
wanna work it off, I won't complain.
Think you can handle the reception desk?\n'Cause if so, I need you there pronto.

I merely check people in? Child's play!
Come round, travelers, and let your jaws
slacken at the fact the great Emile has
prepared rooms for you all!

You've done well to come to the great
Emperor Emile's inn! Rejoice, for I have
prepared a fine room for you at a very
reasonable discount!
Thanks for that, frie—HEY! What part of\nthis qualifies as a reasonable discount?!\nI can't even count all these zeroes!
You dare complain about a price the\nemperor chose for you?! A man has to\nmake money somehow, you know!
Like I give a crap about your wallet!\nThis is a total rip-off, and you know it!
How dare you speak that way to an\nemperor! Now pay that bill before I\nhave you dragged off to the gallows!
What the hell do you think you're doing?!
Stupid little ingrate... I was TRYING to\nhelp the man!

You're clearly not cut out for the kind of
work I do here—and possibly not any
kind—so it's time for you to go ply your
trade somewhere else.
Still, I know you tried in your own way,\nso I'll give you more time to pay off what\nyou owe to me.
He thinks he's doing ME a favor? Ha!\nBut fine, then. I'll just find another job.
I'm sorry, but I don't think you're the\nright fit for this job.
Got no time for folks what don't have\nexperience. Go bother someone else.
Do you even know HOW to wash a dish,\nyou useless clod?!
I can't believe this... I haven't managed\nto make a single rupie!
These people must be blind to not see\nhow I overflow with talent and potential!\nWhy, it oozes out of me! OOZES, I say!

Guy's pactbound dragon bailed on him,
and then the brother he thought was a
huge chump waxed the floor with him.
Woof! Talk about your rough days.
How come we get saddled with a lousy\ncommander like that? Hell, I'll take a\ntraitor prince over a loser prince any day!
It seems I'm a loser here as well...
Oh, blast it all! Why do I have to be hungry\nat a time like this?!
Do you need something to eat, sir?
I was painting over there when I heard\nyou talking to yourself.
Here. You can have half of my sandwich.
You think to show ME charity? What\nmanner of chump do you take me for?!
Oh! Um, right. Sorry about that.\nIt's fine if you don't want any.
Well, I suppose I can appreciate the guts\nit takes to offer your own food to someone\nof my caliber, so...gimme.
Ha ha! Wow, you really WERE hungry!
Excuse me. Is this painting for sale?
Yes, of course! ...Sorry, sir, but I have\nto get going. Business calls!
Oh, certainly! Thank you very much!
(That dreck is making money? ...Wait.\nWait a second. I can work with this!)
You there! Hand over your art supplies!
B-but they're the tools of my trade, sir!
The people's possessions are my\npossessions also! Now quit your whinging\nand fork 'em over!
No, wait! Ugh, what a pushy little man...
...Now THAT'S what I call a painting!
You there! Put this painting up with your\nother paintings for sale—and be certain\nto display it in the front!

Such fine touches! Such bold composition!
I've never seen such a vivacious picture
of the sea before. You absolutely must
sell it to me!
Freely and gladly! You have a gift, my\nboy, and I would love to come by again\nonce you paint another.
I sold it...and even better, someone\nactually praised my work!
THIS is how I'll raise the money I need!\nTime to paint like the wind!
That about covers your little stay.\nYou really made a killing out there.
Your paintings are the talk of the town.
Oh, that was nothing for someone so\nhandsome and talented as I. Now good\nday to you, innkeep!
Here I thought this place was a right\ncesspool of humanity, yet there are so\nmany who appreciate the fine arts!

Saint Lotier has risen in the ranks now
that it has acknowledged the value of my
paintings! It is now less of a cesspool
and more of a...cesspuddle.
It seems you're finally starting to\nunderstand how wonderful this place is.
Mercury?! Why are YOU still here?!
I've been keeping watch to make certain\nyou didn't turn tail and flee.
Do you know why there are so many\npeople in Saint Lotier who love and\nappreciate the fine arts, Emile?
Because a bunch of people with good taste\nflocked here?
No. It is because Zacharias has brought\nand maintained peace in this land.
Peace allows people to do more than just\nsurvive—it allows them to thrive and\nappreciate the finer things in life.
Are you saying the reason no one ever\nappreciated my talents was because my\ncountry was in disarray?
If the empire had been peaceful, your\ntalents might very well have been lauded.
Everything hinges now on what you feel,\nand how you act upon those feelings.\nSo then, what will you do?
You say people will start to appreciate me\nif the country is more peaceful, sooo...
SO BE IT! As emperor, I will see to it that\nmy nation is the most peaceful anywhere!
Wait, Emile! It won't be that simple!\n...Oh, there he goes again—and still\nas selfish as ever, sadly.
However, he HAS grown, even if by a little.
